### Failure Mode 4: No Test for `cleanupGroupMetadata()` When Groups Partially Expire

- **Risk**: HIGH
- **Code Location**: GroupCoordinatorShard.java ~line 983-1004
- **Description**: The `cleanupGroupMetadata()` method iterates over all groups and deletes those that `shouldExpire()` returns true for. However, existing tests only cover the happy path (group expires, all offsets cleaned up, group deleted). There is **no test** for the scenario where:
  1. Only some groups expire (mixed expiration state)
  2. A group expires but not all its offsets can be cleaned up (partial offset cleanup)
  3. The cleanup process encounters an error mid-execution

The test at line 1365 (`testCleanupGroupMetadataForConsumerGroup()`) does not verify the rescheduling behavior or error resilience.
- **Proposed Test**:
  ```java
  @Test
  public void testCleanupGroupMetadataWithPartialExpiration() {
      GroupMetadataManager groupMetadataManager = mock(GroupMetadataManager.class);
      OffsetMetadataManager offsetMetadataManager = mock(OffsetMetadataManager.class);
      Time mockTime = new MockTime();
      MockCoordinatorTimer<CoordinatorRecord> timer = new MockCoordinatorTimer<>(mockTime);
      GroupCoordinatorShard coordinator = new GroupCoordinatorShard(
          new LogContext(),
          groupMetadataManager,
          offsetMetadataManager,
          mockTime,
          timer,
          GroupCoordinatorConfigTest.createGroupCoordinatorConfig(4096, 500L, 24 * 60),
          mock(CoordinatorMetrics.class),
          mock(CoordinatorMetricsShard.class)
      );

      SnapshotRegistry snapshotRegistry = new SnapshotRegistry(new LogContext());

      // Group 1 expires, all offsets cleaned
      ConsumerGroup group1 = mock(ConsumerGroup.class);
      when(group1.shouldExpire()).thenReturn(true);

      // Group 2 does NOT expire
      ConsumerGroup group2 = mock(ConsumerGroup.class);
      when(group2.shouldExpire()).thenReturn(false);

      // Group 3 expires, but only partial offset cleanup
      ConsumerGroup group3 = mock(ConsumerGroup.class);
      when(group3.shouldExpire()).thenReturn(true);

      when(groupMetadataManager.groupIds()).thenReturn(
          Set.of("group-1", "group-2", "group-3")
      );
      when(groupMetadataManager.group("group-1")).thenReturn(group1);
      when(groupMetadataManager.group("group-2")).thenReturn(group2);
      when(groupMetadataManager.group("group-3")).thenReturn(group3);

      List<CoordinatorRecord> records = new ArrayList<>();

      // Group 1: all offsets expire
      when(offsetMetadataManager.cleanupExpiredOffsets(
          eq("group-1"),
          any(List.class)
      )).thenAnswer(invocation -> {
          List<CoordinatorRecord> recs = invocation.getArgument(1);
          recs.add(GroupCoordinatorRecordHelpers.newOffsetCommitTombstoneRecord("group-1", "topic", 0));
          return true;
      });

      // Group 3: partial offset cleanup (returns false)
      when(offsetMetadataManager.cleanupExpiredOffsets(
          eq("group-3"),
          any(List.class)
      )).thenAnswer(invocation -> {
          List<CoordinatorRecord> recs = invocation.getArgument(1);
          recs.add(GroupCoordinatorRecordHelpers.newOffsetCommitTombstoneRecord("group-3", "topic", 0));
          return false;  // Not all offsets expired
      });

      CoordinatorResult<Void, CoordinatorRecord> result = coordinator.cleanupGroupMetadata();

      // Should only delete group-1, not group-3 (partial cleanup)
      verify(groupMetadataManager, times(1)).maybeDeleteGroup("group-1", any(List.class));
      verify(groupMetadataManager, never()).maybeDeleteGroup("group-3", any(List.class));
      verify(groupMetadataManager, never()).maybeDeleteGroup("group-2", any(List.class));

      // Verify rescheduling
      assertTrue(timer.contains(GROUP_EXPIRATION_KEY));
  }
  ```
- **Coverage Delta**: This test exercises the filtering logic in `cleanupGroupMetadata()` (lines 986-994), the conditional `maybeDeleteGroup()` call (line 991), and the reschedule behavior (line 1002). It specifically tests the branches where `shouldExpire()` varies and `cleanupExpiredOffsets()` returns false.

